tion abnormalities."}, "clinicalApplications": ["Screening for autonomic neuropathy in diabetes", "Assessment of dysautonomia in Parkinson''s disease", "Evaluation of small fiber neuropathy", "Monitoring autonomic symptoms in POTS and other autonomic disorders", "Research outcome measure for autonomic disorders"], "actions": {"minimal": "No specific intervention indicated. Monitor as clinically appropriate.", "mild": "Clinical monitoring recommended. Consider targeted evaluation if specific domain is elevated.", "moderate": "Autonomic function testing recommended. Consider referral to autonomic specialist.", "severe": "Comprehensive autonomic evaluation strongly recommended. Referral to autonomic specialist indicated."}, "limitationsAndConsiderations": ["Self-report measure subject to recall bias", "Symptoms may overlap with non-autonomic conditions", "Not diagnostic; positive screen should be followed by objective autonomic testing", "Domain scores help localize dysfunction but require confirmation with specific tests"], "references": ["Sletten DM, Suarez GA, Low PA, Mandrekar J, Singer W. COMPASS 31: a refined and abbreviated Composite Autonomic Symptom Score. Mayo Clin Proc. 2012;87(12):1196-1201.", "Suarez GA, Opfer-Gehrking TL, Offord KP, Atkinson EJ, O''Brien PC, Low PA. The Autonomic Symptom Profile: a new instrument to assess autonomic symptoms. Neurology. 1999;52(3):523-528."]}'::jsonb)
