ng health status in clinical practice", "Monitoring treatment outcomes", "Health economic evaluations (QALY calculations)", "Population health surveys", "Clinical trials outcome measure"], "limitations": ["Does not capture all aspects of health (e.g., cognition, social function)", "Index values require country-specific value sets", "VAS may be influenced by current mood and expectations", "5-level version is more sensitive but may increase respondent burden slightly"], "references": ["Herdman M, Gudex C, Lloyd A, et al. Development and preliminary testing of the new five-level version of EQ-5D (EQ-5D-5L). Qual Life Res. 2011;20(10):1727-1736.", "EuroQol Group. EuroQol - a new facility for the measurement of health-related quality of life. Health Policy. 1990;16(3):199-208.", "\u00a9 2009 EuroQol Group. EQ-5D\u2122 is a trade mark of the EuroQol Group."]}'::jsonb)
