    '[]'::jsonb, '{"scoringMethod": "The FIQR uses weighted domain scoring: (1) Physical Function (Q1-9): sum raw scores and divide by 3 (max 30 points). (2) Overall Impact (Q10-11): sum raw scores directly (max 20 points). (3) Symptom Severity (Q12-21): sum raw scores and divide by 2 (max 50 points). Total FIQR = Function + Overall + Symptoms (range 0-100).", "domainScoring": {"function": "Sum of Q1-9 \u00f7 3 = 0-30 points", "overall": "Sum of Q10-11 = 0-20 points", "symptoms": "Sum of Q12-21 \u00f7 2 = 0-50 points"}, "clinicalSignificance": "Higher scores indicate greater fibromyalgia impact. A change of approximately 14% from baseline is considered clinically meaningful. Scores >45 generally indicate substantial impairment."}'::jsonb)
