    '[{"value": 1, "label": "Stage 1 - No Cognitive Decline", "points": 1, "description": "Patient appears normal clinically. No complaints of memory deficit. No memory deficit evident on clinical interview."}, {"value": 2, "label": "Stage 2 - Very Mild Cognitive Decline", "points": 2, "description": "Patient complains of memory deficit (forgetting where they placed familiar objects, forgetting names). No objective evidence of memory deficit on clinical interview. No deficits in employment or social situations. Appropriate concern about symptoms."}, {"value": 3, "label": "Stage 3 - Mild Cognitive Decline", "points": 3, "description": "Earliest clear-cut deficits. Objective evidence of memory deficit on intensive interview. Concentration deficit may be evident. Decreased facility remembering names, retaining information from reading. Decreased performance in demanding employment and social situations. May get lost traveling to unfamiliar locations. Denial and mild-moderate anxiety often present."}, {"value": 4, "label": "Stage 4 - Moderate Cognitive Decline", "points": 4, "description": "Clear-cut deficit on careful clinical interview. Concentration deficit on serial subtractions, decreased knowledge of current events, deficit in memory of personal history, decreased ability to travel alone and manage finances. Orientation to time and person preserved. Denial dominant, flattening of affect and withdrawal observed."}, {"value": 5, "label": "Stage 5 - Moderately Severe Cognitive Decline", "points": 5, "description": "Patient can no longer survive without some assistance. Unable to recall major aspects of current life (address, phone number, names of close family members, school attended). Some disorientation to time or place. Difficulty counting backward. Retains knowledge of own name and generally spouse/children''s names. No assistance needed for toileting/eating but may have difficulty choosing proper clothing."}, {"value": 6, "label": "Stage 6 - Severe Cognitive Decline", "points": 6, "description": "May occasionally forget spouse''s name. Largely unaware of recent events. Sketchy knowledge of past. Unaware of surroundings, year, season. Difficulty counting from 10. Requires substantial assistance with ADLs. May become incontinent. Diurnal rhythm disturbed. Recalls own name. Personality and emotional changes: delusions, obsessive symptoms, anxiety, agitation, possible violent behavior."}, {"value": 7, "label": "Stage 7 - Very Severe Cognitive Decline", "points": 7, "description": "All verbal abilities lost, frequently no speech (only grunting). Incontinent of urine, requires assistance with toileting and eating. Loses psychomotor skills including ability to walk. Brain no longer able to tell body what to do. Generalized cortical and focal neurologic signs and symptoms frequently present."}]'::jsonb, NULL,
